\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you tell me your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Ernest Edgar Perkins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And you know live at 26 Leverton Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 NW1?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 NW - NW5.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And you're a widower?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When did you get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - 1912.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What year were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 18 - 1889 - 1887.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 Where about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well I was born in Cardiff - and brought to London as a baby of - just about eighteen months old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
So you lived for about eighteen months in the house where you were born in Cardiff and then you were brought to London - where did you live then when you first came to London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I couldn't tell you as a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What's the first house you can remember living in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 My first house was in Kelly Street in Cam - Camden Town. Kentish Town. They're Georgian houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 It's a little circular street isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. Number twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Until I - joined - the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well I give me age as eighteen and I was only fifteen and a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In 18 - 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long were in the Army for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Off and on for twenty-eight years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What do you mean by off and on - what was the off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - I came home from the Boer War. 1901 as a bugle boy. Then the - death of Queen Victoria. Still a bugle boy. And - I left and we
nt back just for a - I left for about a year or two and went back. In the Die Hards - the Middlesex at Mill Hill. Then the - after the funeral of Queen Victoria - King Edward, we knew as Teddy - grand old man - well, middle aged man then he was. The son o
f Queen Victoria. We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
t in mourning for twelve months before he was crowned King. By then I was a full - full blown soldier and - I was living with my mother in Kelly Street.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And you stayed a soldier for twenty-eight years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Twenty-eight years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How many? One I think. Yes, see interviewer's notes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 fact, 3 brothers or 3 sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 One brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. Died in infancy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was he older or younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He'd be younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Can you remember why your family moved from Cardiff up to London - you can't remember? Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When I was born - no, but I know how old he was when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How old was he when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Ninety-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What year did he die.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember roughly how long ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 It'd be somewhere in 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And he was ninety-two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Herefordshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What was his occupation? What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh he was the horseman. He - he knew all about horses and stables. He had several horse cabs in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he have any job that you can remember before he became a horseman or afterwards or was he always a horseman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He - to my knowledge he always knew all about horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he do any part time jobs do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 There was no part time jobs in them days. Either had a job all day or not have it at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember him ever being out of work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, there were times when - things were bad, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember what sort of time that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 It would be - when - perhaps - more in the winter for him. When there wasn't so many people about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. But I know how old - she was eighty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And when did she die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh two years after dad - that'd be '10 - '11 - '12.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I think she came from Her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she have any jobs before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - she was parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 maid. She knew all about domestic service - she knew what they had to go through - getting up at five o'clock in the morning to wash the stone front steps with cold water and 
not go to bed 'til twelve o'clock at night. I knew all about that myself, I'll tell more about that perhaps later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That I can't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she have any part time jobs do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, there was no part time jobs. No, if you didn't - I you had a job you worked all day or you could do without the job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember how many rooms there were in the house at Kelly Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Four. Four. But I've been away from there for a few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did anyone else besides your parents and yourself and your brother live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. One time we had a lodger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember when that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I was a - serving in the Army then. I come home and I wanted to go to my bed and mother said, oh
, I didn't expect you home so soon. I've got a lodger. Oh, I said, that's all right - I can sleep on the couch downstairs. And the lodger only paid for four meals a day, his washing - and - everything attended for twelve and six. He had a room, four meals
 a day and his washing done. For twelve and six. 'Course that was a lot of money in them days. And it was a great help to me mother
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother have anyone helping her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no, she always - she wouldn't have any help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember her doing any particular things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh - it was nothing to go home and find her doing something - she was never done. She was a great cook - she could make us the old time - bread and butter pu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 dd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ings that I used to take with me. She'd never thr
ow bread away. She always had a bread and butter pudding. She'd make the old suet puddings and - we had a wash boiler, out the yard. She used to say to me, Ernie, get the sticks and light that - the old boiler and she'd boil all the washing. Then after th
at she'd wipe it out, put fresh water in and bill the puddings. And perhaps after that a pigs head and make her own brawn. She never bought anything and she - without she cooked it herself. You know, she - was a good welsh cook. She had been a parlour}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 maid in - Caduggon Terrace. Off Sloane Street. She'd been a parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 maid, my father a young man he - I suppose a bit of a soldier too I suppose, he courted her as a parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 maid. He used to tell me that's where he used to go for a buckshee dinner after - she'd 
served the guest she used to come down and go into a pantry and there was always a nice bit of buck}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 she dinner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother or father mend or make your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 All our clothes were made by our mother. That's why she was never done. She - e
xcepting our Sunday suit - which was a Norfolk suit with a belt and - britches with long stockings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did she get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 She - in Gardners. It was known in Edgware Road - Gardeners Corner. You could get a suit - a man's suit for two pound. A 
boy's for one pound ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about shoes - did you buy shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh - they were - not too cheap but - if you had a new pair of shoes and you went to ; chapel you'd be afraid to put 'em on 'til you got to the chapel. So you tied the laces round your neck and carried them to the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You'd walk barefoot would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. To save the boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever have secondhand shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, mother wouldn't have anything secondhand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He was handy man - he - always helped her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he help her with the cleaning or the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not with the cooking. Him and I used to clean the knives every Saturday and the boots. And I - to this day, clean my boots under he
re. You look at any of my boots - they're all cleaned underneath between the heel and the - sole. I - my father - after I cleaned the boots would examine every one. I had to clean all the household. As many people in the house and - the lodgers included a
nd he'd examine them, if I hadn't cleaned underneath he'd give me a clip under the ear and tell me to do 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you father do the fires do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - I'd light the fires or mam or dad or father would, whoever was in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You say he was a handyman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He was - pretty - he used to paint and decorate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he ever dress or undress you or bath you when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Mother done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your father ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh he'd come up - if he felt in the humour and - talk about - the Boers or - wild animals or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he ever take you out by yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. That was his - one of his proud possessions to have a go - we used to go - he bought me a little}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349  box once in - Samuels the Jewe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
lers for half a crown. Very cheap watch but - made more noise than - ticks. And he took me by Big Ben once. I remember pulling out me watch and looking in Big Ben and saying father, Big Ben's wrong by my watch. And he - he laughed
 at me and he said, well, that don't tell bad time. He said the people in there - might tell bad things but the old clock tells the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he mean in the Houses of Parliament?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. And do you know, don't know whether I should say this now - 
the - there's a crack in that bell a quarter of an inch thick - today. And there's words carved - carved on that bell. When it strikes the hour it strikes four times - that's the quarters. Oh Lord this hour my footsteps guide and by th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  power no foot shall slide. That's the words to the tune.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And that's carved on the bell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
That's carved - and the little hand is nine feet and the big hand is fourteen feet and the figures are three and the circumference is thirty-two feet in diameter. Big Ben - it'
s named after Ben Johnson, the man that built the clock and - I think the man in Pall Mall - Dewers were the people as looked after it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your father ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well I - I suppose he did you know. We - were a
lways together - he took us - mother was never one for wandering - the only time she went out was when dad used to take her out for a box of Guin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15271725\charrsid11754349 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ess. We called it a box in them days. It was a casket. We was allowed to go in with 'em and we'd have a sip at
 it. But of course the law came along later on and wouldn't allow children in. But we were allowed to go and sit in them early days. In 1900 and 1901 - '2 - right up 'til about 1906 and '07. But going - there was a bar for - women only, there was a bar fo
r mothers and children, and the pub bar which became the four ale bar because the price of a pint was fourpence - so they called it the four ale bar. In Lloyd George's time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember your younger brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Very, very little. I was away most you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember ever helping him to do things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I my have done. You can't take the years - no. It's not like if you had kept - had a diary kept for that purpose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In schooldays - yes, you - you wasn't in bed by half past seven you were - you got a spanking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When I was very young but - when I got - five, six or seven I could go to bed myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you sleep in the same room as your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh in a separate room. We always had a - a little what we called a night light, she used to put it in a saucer and it woul
d burn - right 'til the next morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You can still get them can't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I believe you can.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we had a tub in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Every Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Then - after the bath. They were hanging on the - the horse - the pulley on the ceiling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there any times when they ate in another room - on any special days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh we had the parlour - the - I don't know what you call - you - call it the lounge today. We call it - we call it - we called it the parlour. We had visitors - we had - always had tea in the parlour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did your mother cook - in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What sort of equipment did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - open range. A - a range - open fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember what time you had breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If I wasn't down to it I went without it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What time did they have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was half past seven the - latest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who was there to have breakfast - were you all there together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Father and mother and myself. The lodger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember what you had to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 It varied. People turn their nose up today at it. We'd - I'd probably go to Sainsbury}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8591574\charrsid11754349 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
s and get - two penn'roth of cuttings. And they were lovely pieces of bacon. But they couldn't be made into rashers - we'd got to the bacon - get two p
enn'orth - Sainsburys, get two penn'orth of bacon and - half a pound of black pudding. Always had porridge - mother made that over night. Porridge first, then bacon and black pudding or bacon - and fried potato-s, bubble and sueak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about the midday meal - what did you have for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh it - whatever was going. If there was a - we always had plenty of soup, as I said, we had plenty of nice baked bread pudding and we were always full.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you come home at dinner time - middle of the day when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh, never - we never had meals in school then. Nor milk or anything. If you wanted a drink you put your hand up and you went out to the cloakroom and - had a drink of water.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your father come back in the middle of the day as well to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Very seldom - if he was out with the horse cart. He'd - he'd try and get as much as he could. Of course - in them days, to have a - a fare or ride in horse cab, well you could go from here to Richmond for only eighteen pence. As 
from Whitehall to Mill Hill for two shillings, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 So if your father was on that long journey he wouldn't come back for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no. 'Cos he'd pull - have a pull up - where he'd give the horse a resf and if he'd - see the pubs on them road
s all had stables in them days. There's only one now I know round here - the Lord Palmerston up at - Highgate - still got the old stables. And he'd have to put the horse in there. He'd have a pint of beer and - top of a cottage loaf and a lump of cheese -
 pickled onions, that would cost him fourpence. His beer would cost him threeha'pence. Pint of beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have an evening meal or tea or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well I belonged to the Boys Brigade. I still got my officers cap with the Boys Brigade. Would you believe that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you come home for tea after school - what time did you come home for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 From school. Always - was nine o'clock, then lunch - or we called it dinner - and then were at - out of school at four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have tea when you got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Straight away mother would have the old pot and the tea -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you have for an evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 As I say, whatever was going. Might be - pigs head or anything - corned beef or whatever was going. 'Cos things are to be bought cheap t
here - there wasn't a lot of money about in them days. So you - you had to buy things very cheap. Mother always - bought - I mean, you must realize - we never went out to shop on a Saturday, not 'til half past ten - eleven o'clock at night. The butchers w
e
re never closed at twelve - until twelve o'clock. And you could buy a leg of lamb - seven pound leg of lamb for eighteen pence. And it would be wrapped up in a breast of mutton. And it'd be thrown over your head - whoever caught it - there'd be a man goin
g
 around the crowd to get the money. You take home this seven pound leg of lamb - eighteenpence - thrown over to your head by the butcher - 'cos he daresn't keep it over the weekend - they had no frigidaires, so out it came, you caught it, you paid for it 
-
 mother give you tuppence Sunday morning to take it to the baker. The baker put it in his bread oven and bake it for tuppence. And steal all your dripping. That was his profit. And - the last baker to do that was in Pernand Street and the Reddows in Kenti
s
h Town Road. Tuppence - take your joint and if - the boy had a bigger joint than you - you keep eye on it when he went for it and - if you could change - it - you'd have - take home a bigger joint with more roast potatoes than what you took in. Well - you
'd talk to him and perhaps he'd put his down to have a game - pitch and toss and - while he was waiting for the baker, and you'd change. You might get a smaller one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother also make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Bread - always made her own bread. We -
 we'd get the man come - the baker - he used to bring - we never went to the shop for bread. He'd bring - if he didn't serve us with bread he'd serve us with flour and yeast. And he'd have a hand cart with a basket and he'd - push it along and give us the
 flour and the - mother made - always made her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she make her own jam as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh many and many la put she made of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about fruit and vegetables - did she bottle those?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Pot herbs - we never called them vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you tell me about pot herbs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well - Sunday morning she'd send us to the vegetab - with a basket, now go and get two penn'orth of pot herbs. Would be carrot, turnip, swede - and onio}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8591574\charrsid11754349 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  - - and - that'd be the pot herbs. And for two penn'orth you'd get enough for a family of four. That'd be on Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she ever bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes, I think she did - she did. She did everything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you ever remember her making medicines - home made medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh we had our own remedies. We had old linseed poultice and - we had - ointments that she made. I had to go and get stinging nettles. She used to boil them and give us the water to drink. Green tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What was that supposed to be good for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Const
ipation. And all them sort of things she had. Remedies that - you'd laugh at today. She - if I had a chill, well - piece of calico. Flanalette - on your chest. Linseed poultice. Bread poultice. Young people - boys, they get boils at the back of their neck
.
 Well they're more carbuncles than boils - was - dad wouldn't say - he'd get a bottle, put it on - over the spout of a kettle - fill it with steam, stick on the back of your neck and draw the core right out. All he did then was a bit of plaster on it, kee
p the cool air off it and you had no more boil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember your family brewing beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Herb beer. Everybody brewed herb beer in them days. That was all made of stinging nettles and - various seed - cones. And you had to tie the cork down with wire - else it'd blow off. That was always for Sunday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Very good. Wish I had some of it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 They don't have very big gardens in Kelly Street do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Very little at the back. None in the front.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was there enough room to grow any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no. You wouldn't bother with it - 'cos they were so cheap in them days. Vegetables. I mean, potatoes was only ha'penny a pound.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember your mother ever buying tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. We never had - tinned. I once remember - courting a young girl and - she said when she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  she'd going to have everything nice - done with tins - out of tins. Well - I said, all right. I'll buy you a present, and I'm not going to 
marry you. Why - she said. Well I said, I've brought you a brand new tin opener. My mother never used to - have a tine opener. You won't make a bacon pudding like she did. That was the end of my courtship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your parents keep any livestock - was there any room for hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No. Oh no. We had a - we had a cock. Christmas time we used to buy a chicken - always alive and - mother often bought a cock but we had the neighbours down on us because it used to wake 'em up at three o'clock in the morning. So
 that put a stop to that. But we bought chickens - or rabbit, and fattened them up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You fattened them up then killed them for Christmas?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I had to build a box for them. And if you had a chicken to fatten you never let it run about you see. 'Cos 
that wouldn't be any good fattening it if you let it run about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How would your father kill - them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - just screw their neck. Let him - let him fly it out for about - ten minutes after. They do you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember how many times a week you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - weekends. And then - oh, perhaps in the week a bit of bulley beef. Or breakfast sausage or something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever get any extra meat from friends in Smithfield or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I did when I grew up, when I was - a man. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 But not while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No. I used to get a turkey you know that because I was very much - like they used to - I used to take 'em their things and that - messages and that. I'd often have a turke
y in a straw bag with an iron skewer put through it to take home for Christmas. But not when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Could, you ever poach a rabbit or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - top of Prince of Wales Road was sheep - grazing. Kenwood and Parliament Fields y
ou could knock off two or three - rabbits. You'd only get ninepence for them at the most. Perhaps sixpence. Oh there were plenty of fields and around here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever take a rabbit home that you'd knocked off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. Oh yes. And I'd get a cou
ple of coppers for bulls eyes off me mother for it. Perhaps tuppence. If it was Saturday I might go and get a faggot and pea - peas with it. Savoury duck and peas. With that tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember ever seeing your mother having less food so that the rest of the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No, I had a very good father, thank God, and he always managed somehow. Though there were dark clouds - he always brought out the silver lining in some - he never let mother go short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No. We - had to wash our hands 'fore meals. We had to hang our cap in the hall. Never bring it into any room - I keep it on now 'cos of the cold. But - we had to wash our hands - 'fore we sat down to any meal. And I believe man
y years - grace was said. For what we are about the receive - make us truly thankful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who would say that - your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Father and mother take it in turn. Then when I got - towards youth I had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Could you eat what you wanted from the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you supposed to eat everything up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was a practice in most homes. Unless you had a pet and you could slyly pass it on to the pet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If there was something on the table you wanted could you just reach for it or did you have to ask?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I asked mam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. Or mam would ask you if you didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you expected to do things like hold your knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well that was - when you were very young you did - make it awkward. It become awkward to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When dad got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes, everyone of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Always same place, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who served the meal up - your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Mother. Hot from the pot - she never - never brought it up - on dishes. She'd bring the pot to the table and serve it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Father first. Then boy. Then mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And then you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well that's me - the boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I was thinking about your little brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, I don't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I can't say, you know, what you call easy today -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What you called easy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We didn't call - we knew she was mother and we knew she was mother and we obeyed her as a mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was she very affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And we loved her as a 
mother. And I don't think I ever had any complaint of my mother. And I didn't notice whether she was soft hearted - if that's the word - or kind hearted or - she was a mother and - all this silly talk about mothers Sunday, it shouldn't be. It was motherin
g Sunday. And that's what mother was. She was mothering. It's not mothers Sunday. Mothering Sunday - or it should be called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If you had any worries when you were a child could you tell them to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Anything. Tell her anything. She knew whether you were telling a lie or the truth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you were a child and had a scrap with another child would she teach you to hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh father would tell us that. Don't be a coward. He hit you, you hit him back. Self defen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9319171\charrsid11754349 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What kind of a person do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 They taught me everything - that was good to teach. And I think up to their death I showed them that they had no regrets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember them ever emphasizing certain things as being very important in life - certain attitudes to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In what age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you were a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What do you mean - attitudes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 As a boy of ten - or twelve - I thought obedience to my pa
rents was most important thing in life. Obedience to me parents and then - obedience to ladies - never to speak to a lady with out taking me cap off. And if I was on a bus, always to get up and give the lady - I was taught that that was the ethics of that
 day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You don't see many people doing that now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, they forget that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - we'd - do it outdoors, unknown to them. But we didn't know the works they know today when we were boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever hear your parents swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. They were too good Methodists.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember, when grown ups were talking, when you were a child, were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no. No. You could sit there but if you - interfered you were told to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If you did something that they disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 My father, if it was serious, would give me a cold bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Make you get in a cold bath or throw it over you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Put in a cold bath and then - send me off to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was the most severe thing that could happen was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Don't think I only had it once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If you did something that was a little bit wrong what would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh he - clip your ear 'ole and tell you you mustn't do that sonny. They were not 
bad - they were never cruel. The cold bath was a kind of a punishment given in them days you know - naughty boys. And girls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother ever smack you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I can't remember. She might have pushed me, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember how you felt when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Like all children you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you resent it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Sometimes you'd run off and - hide. And wouldn't come in for a long time. That sort of thing. Them things I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You'd say you got most of your ideas about life from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
I got all my ideas from me parents. Not anything about sex. The sex was not taught in school. You didn't sit in the same room as a girl in school. There was a - separate girls - separate room for girls, separate for boys.
 The playground the girls had their own, the boys had theirs. Separating was a tall high wall. Like a jail wall. And you never got - you were never taught sex. But - my father - I didn't know anything about sex. Not until I was sixteen or seventeen. Seven
teen. And then my father told me one or two things - about - for men - mixing with men. Mother never told me anything about sex at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not much - just - perhaps mother make a birthday cake or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh from - uncles and aunts and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have any guests for your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh always had a birthday party. I could choose the boy I'd like to bring you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh that was a great family day. You never went out at all that day. You'd never go visiting. They wouldn't allow you. You might - the only time you go out at all was to chape
l. But that was a real day - family day. Dad wouldn't take mam out for a drink that day. It was all - just the family. No visitors. You had your little Christmas cake and - you had your bit of fun, your spin top or whatever you got. You put your sock on t
he end of the bed. It was a s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2317653\charrsid11754349 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ocking then not a sock. And - you had your regular family Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And you liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Kids you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I played the cornet. We had a piano - in the parlour.
 And - dad was a great piano player. He learned me to play the cornet. He'd been a bandsman. In his young days. And now - that's how I learned to play the bugle. I learned that in the Boys Brigade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 It must have been easy for you having learnt the cornet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was there anybody in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we all had - songs - old fashioned songs like Da}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2317653\charrsid11754349 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 sy. Marie Lloyd songs and Vesta Tilley songs. We Georgie Wood songs. Talbot O'Farrell. All them old fashioned songs. Bluebells we gather
. And - take them and be true, is the next line but - we never sang - only the old time musicals.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever sing round the piano together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I - I could - vamp a bit then on the piano myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your parents play games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we had ludo, sn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2317653\charrsid11754349 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 aks and ladders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would they play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes, I - I - I think books has been a - a great help to me in my old age. I read great books. I read Herschels, Darwin 
- them sort of - I never read rubbish. I read - any book of historical value. I used to read - we had plenty of them. We used to go down Farlington Road on a secondhand bookstall - buy 'em for a penny or tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do on Saturday evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh well, we - be indoors. Perhaps if you were the eldest you looked after the younger ones while mother and dad - well, we - mother - when you grow up a bit bigger you went with mam and dad - stand outside or - perhaps ten o'clock come, if you were 
a bigger boy, you'd be up with her while she bought the joint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever do that for her - did you ever go and do the shopping for her on a Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no, you go and get the vegetable. Two penn'orth of pot herb. You wouldn't - ask for
 vegetables. Please can give mam two penn'orth of pot herbs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well if they were good family used to go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you spend it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We used to go to a morning service. Then we had the - Sunday school was always th
ree o'clock - not in the mornings like they are now. And you had a little text. The Lord is my shepherd - and a little picture. Or some other thing. And you had to take that home to prove to your mam that you'd been to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long were you there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
An hour. Yes. And we'd have a penny to put in the plate. We had to go up to a table and put the penny in. Sometimes I'd pretend to put the penny in and I'd keep the penny for sweets. My sister would do it - do it the next Sunday. See then
 the one she'd say, it's your turn. And I'd go up, pretend to put the penny in. And keep it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How old was your sister - was she younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh younger - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You just had one sister did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. We - always had to go to Sunday s
chool and of course the rest of the day was indoors. No television set. No wireless. But - you had a piano you played that or if you had fiddle or a - you could play that. There was no - what you call 'em - guitars them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go to church Sunday evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. We - the young ones never went. The vicars didn't like children Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You told me you had different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh you had your best suit. Always had a best suit. If you were a poor family - mother would put them in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2317653\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 pawn on Monday. Get a few shillings and - they'd always be out for - on Friday night or Saturday morning when father handed over the pay. For you for Sunday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not at - indoors. You could read. We had
 several - boys own magazine. The Boys own. Them old magazines. The Strand. Magazine. Wield World - and 11 them old - but you were not allowed to read dad's papers. He used to get - a yellow pink - a pinkish paper. Called the Police Gazette. They don't pu
blic that now. And John Bull. And you wasn't allowed to read John Bull up 'til you turned fifteen or sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 So they thought it was wrong to work or play on a Sunday did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we didn't - they didn't think it was wrong, it was the custom. Min
d, if mother had to go anywhere we'd be - we'd have a game on our own I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother and father go to the Methodist church as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they go regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You say that children weren't welcome in the evening to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. It was adults service you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they go with you in the morning then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If you were in the choir - then you went to the evening of course - you'd be about eleven or twelve then you see. You got hal
f a crown a week for being in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You said that you used to go on Sunday school outings but what other social activities organi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2317653\charrsid11754349 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ed by the Methodist church did you take part in - was it a Methodist chapel or a Methodist church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well chapel we called it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What other activities did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh well - we'd have games in the hall. What - what we call ping-pong then. Which you call tennis now - 'cps that's where tennis originated from - the old - 'course that originated f
rom Charles I. He stated that by hitting a bat and a ball in the Mall and - that's it. That's how it came but we had the ping-pong. You call it table tennis now. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I was in the choir. I was in the choir I think for about seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How often did you have choir practice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Once a week. That was on a Wednesday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 So that meant when you were older you sang in chapel on a Sunday night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh often, if you had a good voice you sang solo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you belong to any other club organi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2317653\charrsid11754349 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ed by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 There was no other club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 There was a Band of Hope wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was - the Band of Hope, that came in with the Methodist Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your family say grace at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Ye
s. And when you was old enough, if you were the oldest boy, you'd have to say it. Yes. We thank the O Lord for this - our food. Whatever the - the grace of our Lord or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Always had to say prayers at night. That was - mother would be there see that you done it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever have family prayers together with the whole family together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not - we were - we were Methodists. Other families may have done you know like Protestants or Catholics but not - not it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 A Unionist. That is the old word for Conservatism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Why do you think he was a Unionist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well it was t
he fashion in them days mostly. You see, the Labour party never came to power - for - oh somewhere about the 1907. There was no trade unions then - and there was no - the word Socialist didn't come in long after that - they were Labour but not Socialists.
 
And my father wasn't one of them sort. He believed in the upper class and the aristocrats - having the rights - as much as anybody else. And I followed his views and I've always - I am today. I can't help it I - I have to say I'm a Conservative now. But -
 dad would always say, I'm a Unionist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother have any views about politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Very little. Women never took part in politics them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You don't know what her views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. No, they didn't - we had no women members or no wom
en in Parl - the politics at all in them days. They - a woman's place was in - at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Before 1919 - yes. I can remember him taking me to the poll in 19 - 1899.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And he voted Unionist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their jobs if they voted differently from their employers - do you think your father was under that sort of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well that was all silly talk. Members - 
candidates used to come in the pubs and buy a man a pint of beer. They used to say, oh he's bought his vote. Well, nothing of the sort. And - your - your employer wouldn't sack you if you voted Conserve - Unionist because he'd be a Unionist himself.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What if you were to vote Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He wouldn't interfere - he couldn't. He didn't know what you voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember your father actually working for the Unionist party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I remember him - I remember - I remember him standing on the soap box
 - preaching Parliament. I remember him once - when Churchill came back from a war correspondent and he started putting up - he put up then for Westminster against a man named Herschel and he - my father was there first. And then Inspector of Police came 
a
nd said, Mr Perkins, you know this is Mr Churchill's pitch? It was at the flatiron square, Army and Navy stores, at the back. And my father said, now you know first come first served. But he said, if he wasn't the box he can have it. And boy'll help him t
o have a word with me if he wants to. That was all Churchill then as a war correspondent - by the way, I've got a cigar in that drawer given to me by Churchill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When your parents weren't actually doing their work how did they spend any free time they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - mother would do housework, sewing, darning and all that. She didn't have much spare time I'll tell you, not in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well he'd be working 'til eight or nine o'clock at night. There was the horses to bed and everything you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 She had the garden at the back. But women never went outside then in them days. I'll emphasi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4619865\charrsid11754349 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 e again, a woman's place in them days was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 So you don't remember her ever going out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 She went out with dad and myself or any other - always drink - but as I say they didn't look for like the young women - }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  women today have the time of their lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You say your father used to get home about eight or nine at night - was that every night of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, nothing - later than that often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would he ever go out for a drink or something after he got home from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, the pubs were open 'til twelve o'clock midnight then. And the other side the river they were open 'til half past twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would he always go out when he came in in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He'd have his supper first. And perhaps I'd be in bed and the - all the children. He might take mam out - just f
or - wouldn't be far to go, just round the corner. Have a bottle of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4619865\charrsid11754349 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ui}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4619865\charrsid11754349 nn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he belong to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Conservative club. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he go regularly to that club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He'd Sunday morning regular.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were women allowed to go to that club - did your mother go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no. No, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 She would stay at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That's - you - that was right - women never went to these places. Not in them days
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He was a great follower -
 football and rugby - like me, I'm a rugby man. I wouldn't give you tuppence for soccer. But rugby, yes. And if you want to know how to watch a good rugby game - get high up as you can in the stands. The further you are away the better you can - follow th
e match. You can follow the match better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he never go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes. That was a special day, the Derby day. Oh yes, the Derby was a great day. You went on the - on the Sunday to see the Derby - known as Derby Sunday. When we had the fa
irground on it and everyone that could afford it would go to Epsom to see the Downs on Sunday and take sandwiches - and you couldn't have no flask in them days but you could buy a ha'penny mug of tea down there or a large one for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would he put a bet on the horses when he was at the Derby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - why not? Oh you - what's the good of going to a race if you don't have a bet. If you haven't got the money put a shirt on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we had
 the - we had to have the hospital saving group - the - what you call the hospital group. That was for family. That was threepence a week. If it - you was on your own that was a penny a week. And you could go, if you were ill, to any hospital you wanted. 
You had a - a blue or a yellow card and if you wanted to go to - university instead of going to the - workhouse infirmary - which you were sent to, if you didn't belong to the group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they belong to any club against funerals or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
You were insured - Prudential and - oh the Prudential was well - advanced by then you know. The Prudential and the Pearl and there was one up North - was - must be - was called the - Refuge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you get on with your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Fine - fine, never had much -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was there one that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
My mother. Oh I looked after me sister. Oh yes. She looked more to me too. Oh yes, I had a great admiration for me sister. And - any boy that tried to - assault her then, or offend her - I - I would - I was ready - I was pretty good with me hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you actually do things for her - help her to get her clothes on and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Ohm - we had to tie up the lace - the string at the back of her stays. 
They were big iron things and we used to put my - I used to put me knee against her back and pull these - tight you know and tie it for her. I used to do it for mother. Big heavy old things with iron things stuck down 'em. We used to - sharpen 'em - take 
them out when they threw the stays and sharpen them up and make a knife of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you were a child who did you play with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who I played with? Oh anybody that was in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would you play in the street or in the yard at the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the street or - there was no fear of traffic. There was no motors then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember what games you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Hop - hip - hopscotch. Used to have - London Bridge at the top, Charing Cross at the bottom and start. One, two, three, four - all }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4619865\charrsid11754349 that. It was all - there was con}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 krs, marbles - marbles was a popular thing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4619865\charrsid11754349  them days. We'd beautiful colo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6491249\charrsid11754349 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 red marbles, we used to get - buy a doze}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4619865\charrsid11754349 n for fourpence. Beautiful colo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6491249\charrsid11754349 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
red marbles. Played 'em. Come - down in the gutter. That's where we wore our trouser knees out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh if you got dirty you were told to wash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you free to play with anybody that you chose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh anybody in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Your parents never discouraged you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh they warned you if they knew of a bad one. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 They - wouldn't let you play with that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. 'Course we never - there was no such a thing in them days as calling children teenage. That's a new word th
at's - I don't know if it's in the dictionary. I doubt it. It might be now but it's only just, as you say. There was no such a thing as Edward or Edward}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6491249\charrsid11754349 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ans or - or teenage and all. You were boys and girls and you had to put up with the rough and the smooth. You took the sugar with the sand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there any youth organisations you could belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not as you get today, no, no. Only in the chapel. There was no youth centres. There was no night schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How would you spend your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
You had your - you'd go to school at half eight in - that time and you'd come out twelve o'clock for lunch. There was no meals at school. There was what you'd call a tuck shop. You could buy sweets or anyt
hing - like that. But outside would be - a - Italian with his ice cream cart at school - or woman with a donkey cart and she'd have hot cakes on it or anything like that. But there were no - no - meals at the school. You - were back again at school at one
 and you were out at - half past three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What would you do after you came out of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Straight home. Wash your hands and sit down to tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go out to play after tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well up until it was dark. Then come in and - it if - time fo
r bed, if it was bath night mother had a big bucket on the range and a big tub - bath tub - like a proper tin bath and you'd bath in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh out in the yard you had - you had rabbits, chickens. You always bought yo
ur chicken alive - three or four months 'fore Christmas. Fattened it up in the yard. I had a lot of pigeons. I was very fond of pigeons.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you race them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. Used to take 'em in a basket from here to Southend. If I didn't go I could put 'em on the guards van, he'd do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 This is still when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes - well, young man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I had a great - fishing tackle but I didn't do a lot of it. Mostly in Highgate Ponds here. But - you caught fish ther
e then. There wasn't so much people about then. Whatever you caught you threw back. Wasn't fit for taking home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go for walks as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we had walks. There was - there was plenty of walks from here to Parliament Hill then. All country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
I never rode a bike in my life. I can't ride a bike now. But I foten fancy a three wheel - three wheeler - tricycle. I'd like to get one of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You said you were particularly interested in rugby - did you take part in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I played rugby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 As a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. I played for the school. And I played for the local village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was there any other sport you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we had the -
 music halls then and for a penny you went up in the gods. And you had two and a half hours music where the - actors and actresses always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6491249\charrsid11754349 sa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6491249\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
to you quite natural - they never held that thing in front of their mouth - they hadn't got it in them days. They 
had to - they were paid only thirty bob perhaps for a - a turn. They didn't get the money they're getting now. And they sang and you could hear them and they looked to you up in the gallery what we call the gods - for their applause. It was there - the ap
pl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6491249\charrsid11754349 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 use of the gallery that made their name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 While you were a boy and still at school how often did you go to the music-hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh once a week. Either the Bedord or the Mole ar the Getty. If you went to the Getties you couldn't go like this with a m
uffler. You had to buy a ha'penny paper collar outside, put it on, do what you liked when you got inside, tear it up. But there was always a man with a box of ha'penny paper collars. I've got some paper collars now. You buy. They're paper. That's one ther
e now. That's only paper
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go to the cinema while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
There were no cinemas. Not when I was a - the talkie - the silent pictures came on about - 1908 - six, seven, eight. Oh yes. That was very cheap - penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Your mother gave you pocket money - was it always threepence every Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh, it all depends if you were - done anything good for - you might get another couple of pennies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you always spend it on sweets or what else would you spend it on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - anything - toys - anything. Toys were cheap then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did anybody outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not relations or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6491249\charrsid11754349 Oh well that's natural }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 isn't it. You wouldn't know what they did you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did neighbours ever come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh there was the neighbours, yes. They liked - like women of all ages, like a gossip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - all the neighbours would never - no neighbour'd let you down in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember what happened when your younger brother or sister were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh you were kept out of the way. You didn't know anything about that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember who came to help your mother - was if a neighbour or a midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We always thought the doctor brought the baby in the black bag. 'Course my mother had been a - a nurse 'fore she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 . She used to wear her chain, all her keys and everything - instruments on the end of the chain. She'd a b
ig apron with big bows at the back, long - white ribbons hanging down from her hat and - she - she was a great woman, she was - she must have been a nurse and - in that case she always had the neighbours to help. They - never went to hospital to have thei
r
 baby. They wouldn't take you in for a confinement in them days. You had to have it - if you had a home you had it at home. 'Course you - if you were poor - you'd go to the - what they know - is known as the infirmary. You might go to a general hospital f
o
r the first day then they'd come and find out could you afford to pay - one pound or two pound a week in them days. If you couldn't you were taken in a horse ambulance to the infirmary and - we - people didn't like to go to the infirmary. They hall had an
 
impression it was part of the workhouse - connected with the workhouse. Therefore if you went there - you - they'd give you pill - they didn't have pills - or they'd give you some medicine and that would put you to sleep. So the women were always afraid a
bout - and the old people today have still got that fear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother and father have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, we had - uncles, aunts and - I don't know what the - well when you say that - when I say that - well as far as I knew a
s a young man - all mother's had their babies in - and of course - I can honestly say for myself, I - quite believed that the baby was brought in the doctor's bag until I was about seventeen years of age. Weall did, youngsters in them days. Either that or
 
the gooseberry bush. You see Or the sork. There were three things that we always - oh - but my - my mother had her baby by the stork. I would say, oh I saw the old doctor bring it in the black bag. And then the other would say, oh mother went out for the 
day and found it under the gooseberry bush. They were the things, and - young men believed it up 'til a certain age. I was nearly seventeen 'fore I began to know anything - the facts of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How much did your mother and father see of your uncles and aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh they were living in the same neighbourhood you know. You wouldn't know - perhaps every other day, perhaps twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they have friends as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we had friends call, we made - that dad made at work or - I made or - whatever -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would they call to see you or would you go to visit them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We'd go to theirs and they'd come to us. If they came to us it meant we had to go to their.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you think your mother and father shared the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother have friends of her own that weren't your father's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, they mixed up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you invited friends into the house would they be offered something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Always. Oh they always would - that was the custom that there'red be very bad manners to let 'em go without something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there any particular occasions when friends were invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Birthdays and such as that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would you say on the whole the friends who came to call were as much your mother's or father's or more your mother's or whose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well they'd be - they'd be a mixed lot you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would people call in casually without being invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well you never did. You never did in them days. You never did in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements - what do you remember your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we'd always have the piano going, nighttimes - sing-song. Knees up mothe
r Brown and all that sort - Down the Old Kent Road and - Oh Antonio - oh we'd always have a bit of fun ane - make your entertainment, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would they go out to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 With any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh often than not. You might not
 be invited as a youngster but - they'd invited them and the responsibility would be with the eldest child to look after the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Lots of people divide society into different social groups - before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one
 group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
There was the social class, yes. We had the upper class - now we knew then as society people. And you had the - working class. And - there were no other class. There was no class distinction like - society kept to their su
rroundings and the working class kept to their surroundings. There was no bitter animosity one with the other as you get today with the different socialist parties where they cutting one another's throat and saying if's the fault of the capitalist - it's 
the fault of the society. It's they that makes society. It's you that makes society. The way you live and the way you act. You're - you're making the society. If you abide by the law and keep in with the laws then you are a maker - a citi}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 en of society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What class would you say you belonged to before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
As I said, I was unionist and therefore I belonged to the working class who kept law and order. And by keeping law and order you were citizen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who would belong to society apart from aristocratic people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh - no the - household - woman - a mother who'd looked after her children would be classes as a second class - person. There was that class in that - that if you were a worker - if you were a white collar man, if you were a doctor or 
a - a nurse of - you were a little above the worker in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Never. I was all - whether it was a - I was always rise my hat to a - a working lady as much as I would - to a - Missus Churchill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother bring you up to raise your hat to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 My mother always taught - and me father. If he got a fare in his cab - he'd touch his cap and say, where to Madam? And then he'd get d
own and open the door and - he'd rise his hat when the lady left the cab or the gentleman. We were taught, not only ladies to touch our hat to, but to gentlemen. Anyone above our-selves. We respected - Ministers. We didn't - respect the man. We respected 
the cloth he wore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you brought up to call people Sir and Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We were always called - to call a lady - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  Lady Madam. And - a single lady we knew as Miss. A boy under the age of fifteen we knew as Master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would you call}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349  a friend of your\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 s in the street Master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Master. A boy was Master. We were always called - if we went anywhere - the shop keeper would say, I'm sorry, Master, I haven't got that today. But a man Sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember anyone calling your own father and mother Sir and Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes. Insurance agents or the tally agent - the man that took a shilling a week from mother for to buy our clothes, we could buy 'em and then pay back a shilling a week. He always come to the door. If I opened the door he'd say
, is your mother in? Never mam. Is your mother in? And - if she went to the door it would be Madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the area where you lived round here who were considered the most important people when you were boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 The most - important person in - early da
ys in any borough they wasn't known as boroughs then - they were corporations. Well we were known as the corporation. Then it - they became boroughs later on. Well would be the Mayor or the Mayoress. The Mayor would be the first citizen of the borough. An
d
 therefore he'd be the first person to be in the borough and - then would come your member, then probably the vicar - not that you had a great respect for the vicar, 'cos - he was the head of the board of Guardians. You see, what you call - welfare state 
t
oday was no such a thing. There was the Board of Guardians. And if a poor mother or a father who were very, very poor and thought their last hope was the workhouse the vicar would be sitting at the head of a long table with the Board of Guardians and the 
m
an would be standing away from the vicar at the far end and the vicar would have the audacity to say, why do you want to come and - to the workhouse. The very fact that he was poor was answer to the fact that he wanted to go in the - and that very same ma
n that probably }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
 that couple - had said at the service, what God has joined together, let no man put asunder. He's the very man that's putting them asunder, 'cos he's sending the women to one - part of the institute and the man to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you actually see that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That did happen. And I protested a lot about it. I was a man - a young man that picked up these quotations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember seeing it happen when you were a boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. I knew - several neighbourhoods aroun
d here that had to go - had to Highgate Hill to the workhouse. That was the workhouse up there. And the infirmary was next to it. And the man was taken and put in the men's compartment and the woman in the woman's. A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 d there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
you got the very thing that vicar said - shouldn't happen - he was making happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 So they didn't think much of the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well never did thing - he was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 a very - aristocratic - or he tried to be - a very a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ri - 'course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 This wasn't your Methodist Minister was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 It's the vicar of the parish. You see, every parish has a vicar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you come into contact, when you were a boy, - with the Mayo -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh if there was anything special on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember who the shopkeepers in your area mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh they were very good friends with families around 'em. They had to be - because you see, they depended on 'em. They depended on the - the neighbourers - where you would run in and get a - penn'orth of tea, a penn'orth of tea, penn'orth of butter, pen
n'orth - ha'porth of condensed milk. You see. You had all these little things a penny and ha'penny a time. And they got their living in that. The shopkeepers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 They were friendly to everyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh the shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who did the clergy in general mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 They - they mixed with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  neighbourers. I suppose they went around their - every day life trying to get more people to join and all that, you see, but the Methodist Minister or non-conformist Ministers, they were very poor. They did
n't get a lot of money. Their colleges wasn't like the - anything like the colleges of the clergy of the parish. There was no such thing as Cambridge or Oxford, they had their own little Methodist colleges you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who did the teachers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well the teachers again were on the - what you might call the white collared class. They'd mix with their social teachers and people of their own grade, such as shop-keepers or - and something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh you never seen
 your employer. He was - he was a mystery man. The employer, he he had his - conversation, trap and pony. You - you never knew where - even where he lived. Perhaps two miles a long way in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What sort of people would you say went to the church and what sort to the chapel - would you say there was a difference between them?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well there was because - if I went into the parish church I wouldn't be allowed to go in to any pew. I'd have to go where the - the church warden put me. Where there wo
uldn't be no name. The Squire, the Mayor, the Doctor, the - some of the big shopkeepers would all have their own pew. A little door to it and their name. They would have their cassocks on the floor to kneel on and their books would always be left in the p
ew. But you wouldn't be allowed to go in there and sit. They were for the special people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 The people who went to the chapel - - they were the working people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh our - our chapel seats were for any. In standard but there might have been one or tw
o who tried to make - they were better than the other but, you know, you get that in all class of life. But they were all good working class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You don't think any of them had a different way of going on - more money or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no. You might have got a foreman there but his money would only been ten shillings more than anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What difference would that make to his family life - having the extra ten shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not in anyway different - nothing much different. He might be try to be - better suit of clothes than the man that o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349 nl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 y had two pound ten - he had two pound suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 There - yes, you get that in all - areas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember any family that was thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes. I've one or two that would come home - we'd have one or two come home that would - have one over the eight on Saturday night and - 'course would cause up a bit of a shindig and of course - the neighboure
rs would - chinwag about it, see, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember a distinction of this sort being made between craftsmen and labourer
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh there was always that. A craftsman was above a labourer - much, it - much more than they are today. A labourer 
today is almost the same as the - mate. He - he picks up his trade from his mate but in my day you had to go in for - to be a craftsman you had to go in for apprenticeship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And there was a definite difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, she - she - did every - as far as I know of her she was a woman that treated everybody alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And your father too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 The minister was - no, no better than the gentleman next}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was your father of the same opinion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 d we all were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you think your mother though of herself as belonging to a particular social class
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No, what - you'd be - you'd still be the - same, don't matter what - if you went on in life. Of course a young would try and better himself naturally. I tried to better myself every time. And - you couldn't expect mother to
 do much about that, she was, the - the house. She was, the one that looked after the house and didn't bother any further than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Outside of our area? Oh yes. We always - put the Minister or the parish peist or a solicitor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He would be called a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 A gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well as I tell you I think before - we always were taught by out mothers that a man in a better po
sition than ourselves was a gentleman. If he acted as a gentleman. But - there were some people mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
used to say who called themselves gentlemen and they're no more better off than a labourer in their manners. But a real gentleman had manners. I would - 
call anybody a gentleman who would help an old lady onto a bus or rise his hat when meeting a lady or give his seat up. He was a gentleman in his manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about a real lady - she would be the same fort of thing would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - a lady - a 
lady - a lady's a ladie the world over. Don't matter what her position or what her - her life is, we were taught that the - female sex were the - ones that we always had to help if it were - there were two people in distress - go for the lady first if the
r
e was a lady and gentleman - go for the lady first. Bring her to the shore. Then, if there was any chance go back to the man. But the lady always came first and that's - well that is on ships. Women and children - why they never put children first there I
'll never understood but - it's women and children because it's quite right - because the woman looks after the child, without the woman the child wouldn't - exist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you think of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
They were a grand body of men. When they went on duty, eight of them, with the Sergeant, they never walked on the payment - they all walked in a single line in the gulley - gutty - gutter. You don't see that today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you frightened of the policeman when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
We were frightened of his leather cape more than the policeman. He caught us pinching an apple - we'd - get a blow of that cape, we never forgot it. I wish they had 'em today but they've done
 away with 'em. You'd always see that cape in the doorway or at against the lamppost but he never left it on the payment at the lamp post. He always - had a little strap and strapped it around the top of the lamp post away from the dog's leg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh that was a regular saving them days. Yes. We were frightened like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How do you think the policeman treated the people in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well the - hadn't the ways and means t
hat the modern police foree had. But the - 1890 police - were very very good. They got a drunk, they - various parts of the district, there was a little shed with a stretcher in. They'd bring that out and put the drunk on the stretcher - if it was a woman
 she had two straps, one across the leg and one across the breast. If it was a man it was one stra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9375840\charrsid11754349 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
. The reason of the two straps - was that the woman was liable to kick her legs up and that wouldn't do, so - they had to strap her legs down. That was the - 
way of conveying - drunks to the police station which we didn't know as a police station, we knew it as a barracks. Police barracks - not police station. And the one here now, the oldest one just here, which is empty now, well - occupied - business and fl
ats, was built in 1785 and still - it used to take the old horse Maria then, two horses towing the black Maria. Oh the policeman in them day was a grand fellow. He was a good fellow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was it a rented house you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 My father bought it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you ever remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, we didn't have it all sugar but it was - we carried on very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We never had what they got today - the - local helps and that but - mother always looked after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no. Oh no. They never went to the Board - we didn't like the 
- Board of Guardians. We had no - inclination to - worry the Board of Guardians. They wasn't on our side. Of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When there was someone in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No, not particular. Not particular - just like to day I suppose. You'd - not - shun them then you seen them or - if you were on the door you went in and shut the door, that sort of - petty - grievance you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember anybody being made to move by people making rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
We never had the music. We had a long horn gram phone but it wouldn't play loud enough to disturb anybody. And the records were round then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You don't remember anybody making an effigy of anybody to make them move off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. We used to make effigy\rquote 
s in local elections. Of the member or something - if the snow was out and - or if there was a local election we'd make an effigy of him and if we supported him we'd put a flag on the around him and carry him arou
nd the neighbourhood singing vote, vote, vote for Mr - so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were you given lessons by one of your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, we had a good schooling. They were known as first, second, third, fourth and fifth standard, there was nothing above the 
fifth in them days. We never called 'em - what they call 'em today, we call 'em standards. You went in the first standard the infants into the second standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I think about six - seven. There was no compulsory to put you - at five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you first started what time of the morning did you go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 About at half past three to four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you come back lunch time - in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh you had to or you didn't get nothing - or take it with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Which did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Now and again - varied. I - vice versa, sometimes take it, sometimes we didn't. All depended what mother - mother had. If she had boiled bacon pudding and boiled plum pudding we'd come back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Be about half past twelve. You had an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What kind of a school was it? Was if a church school or a board school or a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 They were called board schools then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was it girls and boys mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No, never. No. You wasn't allowed to go into the girls playground. There was always - between the boys playground and - and the girls a wall as big a jail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How far was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh if it was two or three miles you walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How far was your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 About a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I could do it as a youngster I think in about ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If I met any other boys on the way you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Wasn't bad at all. Good old schoolmaster - you'd never see him without that swishy little cane in his hand. It was a good thing. And you had it sometimes you had it on the pa
lm of your hand, sometimes you had it on your bottom. There was no hesitation. And if you - had to wait your turn for the cane you were put in the corner and you wasn't allowed to look at the class, you faced the wall right in the corner.. But you was exp
ectation of a nice - wash ups to swishy cane. Oh yes, that was a good thing to have in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How many teachers were there at your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I couldn't tell you. Each class had one - each of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life - like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes, that was read out in the school. 'Course, it was compulsory for us to have church service, that was compulsory. And then you filed into your class and - you would have a - there was all - the teacher alw
ays had a favourite boy. Most teachers have I suppose. He'd come out with the chalk and the black, board and - save the teacher getting up he'd do the blackboard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they emphasise things like tidiness as being important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes, tidiness, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh that was a - a very severe thing. Yes, you - you were booked if you were a quarter of an hour late, you were booked. And that - was always read out at the close of each quarter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they teach you to speak in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Not so much the tone - you wasn't taught the - the - what'll I'll call it, dialect - dialect? Oh you were taught the pronunciation but it didn't matter - id didn't matter about your dialect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If you did something the teachers disapproved of you'd get punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well you'd get punished either with a telling off or with a - swi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11627909\charrsid11754349 t}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ch - I remember receiving six of them once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - a boy called another little boy a nasty word and I didn't like it and I punched him in the nose. And his nose bled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And you got the cane for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I got six on me bottom. And I showed 'em to me dad. He said, sever you right, you should behave yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were the girls punished differently from the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I think they were pun - they had the cane. 'Cos now - not on the bottom. Like the boys. They had it on the palm of their hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother and father show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, he always wanted to see, when we broke up, or he was pleased to get a letter from the schoolmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they ask you what you'd done in the course of a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, ask you questions, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. Unless accidentally you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did all the other children at your school come from the sort of homes as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh pretty near. ;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Never knew what a gang was in the - days. It's only in this modern age we hear about gangs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there ever any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
There was - lots of things like that you know. You get that - again - again you get that in any part of any town in any country. There's always the left out you k
now, the - right at the back one. I suppose they put that - we put that one down as a - oh he wasn't all there or - he's a bit slow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go on to another school after that or did you stay at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I - when - at old John Ellis - William Ellis' school all me time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No. I wish I'd - I'd a little more of it. I'm very quick at picking up and - I think if I'd had a better education I - I would have gone in for politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11627909\charrsid11754349 But you think you benefit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ed from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Morning papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you have to do for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh for - two and six a week then. Not what they're getting now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What time did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Seven now - six or seven in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Might take me to about - on the Sunday morning - two hours. On the weekday morning only one paper to each you see - an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
You applied for it. Perhaps you'd get a tip with a boy at school was leaving school and he was leaving the job and you fly around there as fast as you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you feel that two and six was enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
It's a lot of money in them days. Oh bless my heart, I could have took you out for the night on two and six. And you could have had a couple of - whisky or gin or port and I would have had enough for a drink the next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do with the money that you earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I put it in the Post Office book. We had a book then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you give any of it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If she wanted it. Very seldom she'd take it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was there anybody else doing the round with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh you was by yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you get on with your employer - how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well he - tell you off now and again you know, you probably - got the deliver somebody's paper or put the wrong one in the wrong house. But he - he was all right
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Very nice - I liked him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can't say I did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Why was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I had a terrible trouble with mother when I got home for breakfast. Used to get the print all on me hands. And it took a lot of ge
tting off. And mother wouldn't believe it was the paper print. She thought I'd been playing about and dirtied me hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did having this part time job alter you attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was the only part time job you had before you left school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 The delivering papers - then I helped the milkman one time. Two bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was that after the papers or before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh with the papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You went on his round with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. 'Cos he used to have pony an
d cart. And - he'd lift the milk of of the churns - big churn, with a little half pint measure - put it in another little can with a lid and I'd have to hang it on the nail. On the door of the house. That saved him getting off his cart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you deliver the papers at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No, no. Milk was delivered any time in the day then. Would be sometimes in the evening. See? And - he'd have his pony and cart and - it might be - five in the evening - six and he'd deliver the morning milk, see. If it 
was a wet day he was always happy. He used to leave the lid of the churn off, so the rain used to make it a little bit more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have to do that on a Sunday as Well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He wouldn't go on the Sunday - he wouldn't deliver on Sunday. Saturday nigh
t you see for Sunday. And you never-never had bottles. It was always a can with a lid, and you hang it on a nail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did having that job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do with the money from that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Same - buy - to buy a bike or whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You didn't help your father before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I was a band boy in the Army. Oh I used to help me father - I didn't put that down as a job. No. Oh I was out
 with the - I took a cab out on me own but that was father's not - that wasn't - I was - that was to do with the family you see in the house but - young boy - at sixteen and a half I joined the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - recruiting Sergea
nt with a lot of ribbons hanging down his hat pulled me up in the street one day. Said I was a fine looking lad, well built, well - and he thought I'd be a very good one for the Queen's Army. And I said I'd like to. He put the Queen's shilling in my hand 
a
nd I couldn't get away from it then. Once I had that shilling the palm of my hand - I was - but he took it back off me. Took me in the pub, he bought a pint for himself I had a shandy. Then I went to the New Scotland Yard, told to strip off and bath and t
he doctor would be along in a few minutes and I was carried off to Mill Hill - the Mid - the Die Hards - Middlesex Regiment.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you tell me exactly what you had to do in this first job as a bugle boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh the - there was the practice. Up at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid685903\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 reveille.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Six o'clock. If you were - could grow any hair on your face you were given two minutes to have it off - to shave. And then breakfast at seven. Cook house bugle boy - perhaps you'd have to blow that. And then after that band practice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long did that go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh, perhaps two hours in the morning. That was the regular - that - no more that day of band prac - two hours in the morning, and I learnt the cornet. And then I joined the band boys. What you call the
 young soldiers. Was in the band. And then I - I went in the band into the regulars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have to do the same things in each of these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, get up the same - reveille.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What would you do after the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well if there 
was no parade you'd be free for the day in barracks. You could apply for a pass out - but - more often than not you stayed in. There was no such a thing as rushing out to - parties or anything. You could have a weekend pass to go home. A}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid685903\charrsid11754349 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 d then I left the Army as an Army reserve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That's be about 1910 - eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you work Saturday and Sunday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the Army? Oh church parade on Sunday. You all fell in in the barrack yard - Sergeant Major - a church of England 
on the right, Catholics on the left, Methodists in the front. Anybody wanted the Methodist. A lot would go to the - fall in with the Roman Catholic parade. Although they were Church of England. And then when they get to the church - I'm sorry, Sarge - I t
hought this was C.E. I can't go in there, I don't know nothing about it. And they'd have to wait outside. That was the way you could - could get a good smoke and - packet of Woodbines was only five for a penny then. Ten for tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How much did you get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Sixpence. Oh, a boy, threepence a week. Sixpence a week - a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How much did you get when you joined the band boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When I joined the band? I got ninepence then. But then it went up to a shilling a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How much were you getting when you left in 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh, only a - it was shilling a day then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do then when you became a reserve soldier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I went home. And helped father again. The old horses and cab.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you have to do now to help your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
I used to take a cab out. I'd got out in - with horse and cab, perhaps Kings Cross or Euston. Or even Marylebone. Or I might go up the West End. But I had one or two regulars. I used to call on them. They - fellow - well Lord Lonsdale was one of my
 regulars. If he didn't take his own cars like - early he had a car but it was a rough car so he - if he didn't get his horse and coach or his groom out, there was something wrong, he'd have me as a cabby and I'd deliver him to Liver - Lever Brothers, Bla
ckfriars Bridge, he was - Director of that at that time. And I had one or two regulars, if not that morning I'd go to the station.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What time would you start your day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh, we wouldn't go to the station 'til about half past nine. And perhaps we'd 
have a maid just come from the country with a box as big as - half house nearly, an old trunk. Iron trunk at that. And we'd have to get that on the top of the cab. And she'd be a maid come up from the country and - she might want to go to Caduggan Square,
 
Chelsea or she might want to go to Charles Street, Mayfair and we'd say eighteenpence, two bob. And she'd look twice in her bag - in her purse when she got the two bob out, 'cos that was a lot of money to a maid - housemaid. Might be old cook - she'd look
 at it too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How many fares a day would you have on average?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well the weather didn't bother us so much - we were well wrapped up with a long cape over our shoulders and we kept the old nag well covered up with a cape. But - you average about twelve fares a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would you go home for your dinner in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, you'd leave the old horse and - in the harness and he'd - put his nosebag on. He'd be all right, he wouldn't move.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you work Saturday and Sunday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not Sundays. Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How much did you get for doing that when you were working for your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - all depends. Father might say, well we've had a good week son, here's ten bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You got on with him well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. He - you 
see, you had to be honest with your father. He didn't know how many fares you had. But he was a pretty good judge. He would tell by the old nag how far she been running.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you think you were happier working for him than you were as a soldier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I was happy at home, yes, always happy at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you were a soldier when you were a boy did you get on with the other boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes. And then - came the first great war. Four o'clock on August 1914, and that night the fourth of August abo
ut eleven - half past eleven somebody knocked at the door. I was in bed. Mother was in the front room, she opened the front room window. Said, who's there? He said, I'm Sergeant of the Middlesex. Does E Perkins live here? Yes she said. Well tell him to be
 
report at Mill Hill at ten o'clock tomorrow morning sharp. And mother - mother got that thing from under the bed and said if you don't go I'll let this drop on you. Anyhow she told - woke me up and told me. Well, I said, mam, I've got to go. I'm on reserv
e. And the week after that I was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid685903\charrsid11754349 F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
rance. And that's how we were called the Contemptibles. Anybody in France from the November the fourth - August the fourth to November the twenty-eight was a contemptible. Because the Kaiser said to William, his son, you
 must wipe that contemptible Army out. We - we we catched on with the name and - we're known today as contemptibles.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And what was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I don't - it was 'orrible. No war has ever been like it since. The last war was a palace to it. We got
 - no clean clothes, no baths, hard biscuits soaked in tea. Then jam put on. Eating in trenches with the rats as big as cats. Eating the dead bodies around. It was 'orrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You were up in the front line were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I was up and I got - lot of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13048768\charrsid11754349 shrapnel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
 wounds in the neck and I was sent back to the base at Rouens and then I said - they told me I was going to London, Mt Thomas hospital, but when I got to Charing Corss I was put on another train to Scotland. To Lee - Leith. Two miles from Edinburgh.
 I couldn't speak for about nine months I had to press a tub}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156612\charrsid11754349 e to speak to anybody, in the t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
rout. But the doctors put that right and - I'm all right. But I - I mean - the last war was a paradise to - compared to - we got lousy and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What sort of shifts did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh, there was no such a thing as shifts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You must have had time off to sleep sometime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You kept - you kept in the dugout what you made in the ground. You never left your trench to you got relief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long were you in the trenches from when you arrived in France?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Maybe two months, three months. Before another battalion could come along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you stay right 'til the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. I went back again - to the battle of the Somme. I got a nasty one in the leg and I come home. And they discharged me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well then I joined the Royal Commissionaires. And - I was with them for many, many years. In them days - we had various jobs. Someti
mes a wedding party at the big hall, sometimes at the big stores, sometimes at Bu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156612\charrsid11754349 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
kingham Palace functions - garden parties and such all. Sometimes just delivering a bouquet. Sometimes - I had to go to America once with some very valuable jewels. And - I t
ook 'em in an old case that I threw this old case about that - nobody bothered. But the jewels were in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you come to join the Royal Commissionaires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I was - it all depended on your Army career. I had a good Army career and three stripes you could join.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How much did you get paid then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
In the Royal Commission - oh the money was a lot better then. It went up to three pound a week. You see the money was rising then all the time. It never rose to what it is today - twenty pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156612\charrsid11754349 Would you have prefer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11156612\charrsid11754349 nc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 e to do anything else or is that what you really wanted to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I - it was more that - more in my line 'cos of the Army service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Because of your Army career you didn't have to do an apprenticeship or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
I had me Army - you had to have a full rank N.C.O. and a good army record. That is if you came out of the Army with a medal we called the Undetected crime or the routine medal we call it. That's a long service medal - which you have to do twenty-two ye
ars 'fore you got. And you never had to have a stain on your character. No Court Martial no - no confined to barracks and no mistakes and - even if you were caught taking in John Bull - or the newspaper - or Reynolds - you wasn't allowed to take them into
 barracks but if you were caught with one in barracks that - that would be a crime. And of course you wouldn't get the routine medal then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 But you got it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I got it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have any trade union or professional organisation that you belonged to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
No, we was - never bothered trade unions or nothing. We wouldn't be caught like that. No, the Royal - Commissionaires was run in a very, very high grade, good character men. I mean, you were left with responsibility. For instan
ce, you might be asked to take charge of a stores and they'd give you a flat on the top of the stores - well that was a big respon - such as - John Lewis, or Swan and Edgars or Harrods. You see, I knew Harrods and Swan and Edgars when th}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156612\charrsid11754349 ey were only one little shop se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
lling cottons - reels - and if you had bought the cotton - reel - cotton of reel - reel of cotton you were - was a penny threeparthings, you give 'em tuppence, they give you a packet of pins in place of the other fathing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you think at that time that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well - the employers - had a great interest in the welfare of the country. They were - they - didn't have so much mass production as they have now. They had to depend on skilled men. By hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you think the workers got a fair deal on the whole or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh they got a very fair deal. There was no interference - 'cos there was no trade unions. 'Course that's going back 'fore my Army career.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Some people say tha
t in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers - you said that applied when you were a boy but did it still apply when you started working - after the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 It applied to the year about - 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That's when it ceased to exist so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
It didn't come 'prentices - after the war they - they didn't seem - they didn't seem to apply it for apprenticeships. They went in for any casual jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you or your wife vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh many a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What party did you vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 The Unionist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What party did your wife vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Always followed me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you or your wife ever feel under any pressure to vote dor any particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Never. I voted on me principles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You were actually a member of the Unionist party were you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. I used to speaker for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Whereabouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh -
 any - particular - my biggest speech - I've been in the - hall at - at Dipland Halls that they would hire or - Marble Arch or any street corner where we thought - a meeting would probably be a success.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your wife take part actively?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you take part in any other political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes, if - there was anything interesting on - we - I would go to their meetings and - but there was always a monthly meeting which I always attended. And I'd sometimes take the chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When you and your wife were not doing your work how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - take the child out. Go for walks in the Parliament Fields, Hapstead Heath. Anywhere where there was beautiful hills and fresh air.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go out together in the evenings very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Often. Very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When did you get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We used to work from say half past six 'til six o'clock in the evening. It'd be about half past six when I got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How many evenings a week would you spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I'd say everyone of them nearly, barring when I went out to the local to get a - a pint of beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 After you left school did you go on living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your brothers and sisters and parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no. No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you spend your Sunday any differently after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, the usual way when we - long as I was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You still went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you still go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you start to take any interest in politics then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, when I - somewhere within the range, sixteen - seventeen, I was a - very interested in politics. 'Course 
we had - what they call the Unionist party then They call them Conservatives now. Conservatism and Unionism were two different parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What was the main difference between them do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - one - the Unionist were real rank loyal Royal
ist, you see. And there was a variation in the Conservative side. They were more of the middle class, the Conservatives you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you spend your spare time any differently after you left school - what would you do in the evenings at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well I don't do - deliver papers - newspapers. See you sold the papers then in the street. You had to run along and shout out - you didn't m-deliver 'em to house to house. You had to sell 'em in the streets shout 'em out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go out in the evening to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Well, game of cricket or whatever - football or - I was fond of - hockey. Oh I played all the games that were going. Marbles. Used to play marbles in the gutter, see, and perhaps go h
ome with a pocket full of marbles and - you'd won all the lot. Game of conkers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would you go to the fields to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Over the fields - go over there to have a chat and a tease the shepherd who was watching the sheep. He was a Scotchman, he brough
t the sheep from Scotland down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh other lads of the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you make any new friends - any boys or girls - at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh it's hard to say now. So many years gone by. I had plenty of friends. Girls I was a bit shy about them. More shy then than I am now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever bring any of your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh, we used to go to one another's houses. I had a particular friends, I used to like to go to his 'cos I always got a piece of bread pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was he your special friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I used to like to go to his house for that reason. 'Cos bread pudding was a great favourite in them da}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349 ys. You never give it to the pig}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 eons. Mother used put a bit of suet and a few raison, sultanas and bake it in oven. I
 was very fond of that - we used to take it to work. And I used to go to a friend's house 'cos his mother was very good at making this bread pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have any other special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes. Had several close friends, yes. And - I ha
d a great - regrets at finding that several of them were killed in the first great war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother and father meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Always brought to meet 'em in the house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did they expect to know where you were when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
I don't - they were stiff about that you know. You hadn't to go too far, used to ask their permission if you wanted to go anywhere a train - a journey or anything. You would never do it without their consent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have to be home at a special time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Ten o'clock at night after - when you were about sixteen - not later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How old were you when you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I think twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 So you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  in 1911?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long had you known your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349  w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was the year that King Edward - King Edward VII took}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349 
 very ill and the end of his re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
n you know. Oh I - I knew her for about seven years. She was - in the neighbourhood you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you meet her for the first time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 She was a neighbourhood you see. Yes, I - I knew her then - oh, I suppose from a little boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Before you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
 did you save up money to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well you could get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
 then, I suppose, lots of people got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  on twenty-five - thirty shillings and two pound a week. 'Course that was a lot of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you save up some beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, but - a lot of it I had to pay the tally man. He used to call once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Who was the tally man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 The tally man was the man that collected the money for anyth
ing you had on - hire purchase. And - you paid a shilling a week if you wanted a new suit you - he'd bring you along a new suit and pay him a shilling a week for it you see. Perhaps you'd mount up to three shillings. Never much over three shillings a week
, you couldn't afford it 'cos your wages would only be as a boy seven and six a week. But it was a lot of money. Lodgers - man getting lodgings in your house he could have four meals a day, his washing done and - his bed for a week, twelve and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your mother and father help you to set up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh they helped in every way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long were you actually engaged for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Very short. About three months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you describe your wedding day - can you remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - yes, beca
use - she wore all white. I wore a Mark and Emery suit that had been well pledged by mother and - carnation. Oh yes, a - I had a loan of a - one of father's horse cabs and my - the wife sat on the seat in the front of the cab with me. And me mother and fa
ther inside with friends and she sat on the cab - with me in her white. And - nearly lost her veil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Whereabout}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  - were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  at the Methodist church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 At the - old Methodist church then in the Prince of Wales Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you get wedding presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember how many guests you had - how many friends came?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 about thirty - forty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go on a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Folkestone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Fortnight. We stopped n
ear the mountain called - the hill called the Sufar Loaf. On the Dover Road. And - had a full fortnight there in Folkestone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did you live after you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Then I - when I took the house in Kelly Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How many years did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Going on thirty-five - forty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you come directly here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How old was your wife when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Same age as me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your wife have a job when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no, she never went to work. No,
 no, they didn't believe in it in them days. A woman's place is in the house. Oh well, now times have changed my dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You had one child did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 One son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When was he born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In Kelly Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember what year he was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 1912 - the end of - about 1912.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was he born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes. They didn't take you in - women had to bear their burdens at home. The hospitals were known as infirmary's then. They were not so nice a place to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you help your wife when she had her baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I was there present. Because - qualified first aid man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no, not quite that. Oh yes, I - I was there present. That was a privilege in them days. Men don't seem to
 want to do that these days. They think it's not their place to - or proper for them to be there - than to sit out in the passage looking at another man who's worried as much as them as to - making - themselves ill for no cause whatever if they were there
 they could see what happened. You'll never have to wait for the nurse to come and tell you if it was boy or girl. You were there - you saw it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember how long your wife was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Only - no more than two or three days. They never let 'em stay three weeks and pet 'em up like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you manage while she was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, I managed myself quite easy. I managed to look after her as well. 'Course she was up the third day and - doing washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did any friends or relations help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Or visit neighbourers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember exactly what they would do to help when she was having the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh the midwife you know, I helped her - I got the water - the hot water and I did everything that was nec
essary and - 'cos to me - it became an experience in the war - second great war 'cos I - I helped to bring a babe into the world in the street you know when - the woman fell with the blitz.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How much did you have to do with your little boy when he was a baby under one year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh I could do anything with him. I could change his nappy or do anything. Yes. I could do all that. If she was busy getting something ready I'd - put him to bed just like as god as she would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever take him out by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes. We never had prams though. I had to carry him. Mother had to carry him in the shawl. We never had prams in them days. To take a baby out in a pram was - belonged to one of the aristocratic - they were very scarce things. And very
 expensive. But a shawl over your left shoulder and under your right arm, you could carry the baby for miles in that. But the men wouldn't have that of course. You just carried them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I'd like to ask you how you and your wife managed the housekeeping in the years before 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 She had all the pay packet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You gave it all to her did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And you get a few bob back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the Kelly Street houses there are four rooms aren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Terraces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have any lodgers or relatives living with you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh yes, as I say, we had a - I had a spare room you see and I had twelve and six, I had a lodger. He got four meals a day, they was all with beer - a bottle of beer and - bread and cheese on the table when he come in late at ni
ght, if he came in late that was his supper. And - 'cos a bottle of beer would only cost tuppence then. Today it costs two bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your wife do all the household things herself or did she have any help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was - I never interfered with that a
t all. I used to bring the firewood home whatever I saw a bit you know and pick it up and bring it home but - and chop it for her. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she do the washing at home or was it sent out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh no, no sending out in them days. No launderettes th
en. You had a Chinese laundry. They were very cheap. But you - we never sent ours their. She had a boiler in the backyard and - she'd ask me to light the fire underneath and then she'd boil the washing and then after that she'd was the boiler out and if t
here was any puddings to boil she'd boil 'em in there while fire was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she make any clothes herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Very good at that. In fact she won a - a first prize of a - a gold thimble - solid gold thimble in - as a first prize. In fact, I tell y
ou the truth, I - foolishly enough I let that gold thimble go - only about two years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And she did all the mending as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. Always put a patch in me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever buy second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 hand clothes in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. I didn't believe in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Shoes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 N}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349 o, I wouldn't wear anybody else}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 's. Being a - a qualified first aid man I didn't believe in that 'cos - that's a great mistake in life for catching disease.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever do anything in the house - any cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well, if she was ill or away - out or - I sometimes send her down to see relatives different parts I'd do it myself. Oh quite capable.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If she was well would you help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I never interfered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever do any decorating or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember making any improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh I put window boxes up and all that - painted the front. Painted the front and all that sort of thing you know. 'Course our rent then - we had - th
e rent of them houses today - four pound a week, ours was only half a crown a week then. You could buy our house then for three hundred. You can't get it today for four thousand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you help with your little boy - did you do things like dressing him and undressing him or bath him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I made him do it himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What age would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Three to four. Oh yes, I taught him all that and made him carry on. No good petting 'em up you know. But the kind, but be stern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever tell him stories or read to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh he always asked for one of them. I ran out of them sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever take him out by yourself without your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh he often took him out - to ease her a bit. She'd be glad to get rid of him while she was doing the housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When he was little did you teach him to do any special little tasks in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh lots of little things you know. Taught him the - what tools were and what they were - used for and the dangerous things. Not to angle - w
ithout experience. Such as that. 'Course we had no telly so - well - wirelesses then you know. Well I don't - I think the first - Savoy Hill wireless I had - the - what they call it - the - oh it was thing you put over your head - your ears - no, earphone
s
 - we used to listen in when they first come out to Savoy Hill. 'Cos 1910 was the big beginning or Marconi and then when they caught Doctor Crippen on the Atlantic who ran away from the Earl Regents Park and wanted for murdur. He was the first man to be c
a
ught by wireless you know. Yes, on the Captain on the ship - wired - then they - 1910 - the streets of London were - flowing with the news. Dr Crippen captured - on the Atlantic. Aboard of a ship. With Mrs Neve. And that made wireless then begin - 'course
 
then they - Marconi got Savoy Hill opposite the Savoy Chapel - the chapel of the - Savoy's - the old Sir Savoy. We had crystal sets. That's the name. Crystal sets we had then. And of course - it'd be dangerous for the boy to touch anything unless he knew 
something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What time did he go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - soon as it got dark. Six o'clock the latest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you put him to bed or your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh she - that was her job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he share the bedroom with you or did he have another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Shared with us 'til he was about three. The bedroom. Then he went to his own. I had to get rid of the lodger then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did he have a bath in Kelly Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh, he had a bath by the fireplace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How often did he have them in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Every Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he have clean clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did you eat your meals in Kelly Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 In the - back room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there any occasions when they were eaten in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Only on Sunday night. We used
 to have tea in the parlour - the front room. Called the parlour in them days. I think you call it the lounge now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What sort of cooking equipment did your wife have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I couldn't tell you. She - all sorts of things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was it a range or a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 A range in the kitchen. And we had a boiler at the back of the range. What used to get us warm water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 All depended. I would - I might, when I started work, wouldn't be home to breakfast. I
'd make a cup of tea and take her up one, 'cos she - I wouldn't tell tales out of school what time she got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you remember what you had for breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Only on Sunday. 'Cos I was home. Oh I - probably pop out - Saturday morning 'rore I went to work and go to Sainsbury}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13386891\charrsid11754349 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
s - two penn - two penn'orth of bacon cuttings, you'd get a - nearly a pound for that. And you'd have bacon and egg and she'd used the rest of it to make a bacon pudding in the week. See, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you have for midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh well if I came home there was always something hot. Yes. Varied - varied. It varied you knows. Fish and chips was a regular Friday. End of the reach then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was that midday or evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Midday. You get ha'oroth of fish and ha'porth of chips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What sort of fish was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Cod and steak - hake, haddock. Happorth of each. A penny over the counter and you had your dinner. And it - and by the time you go out and go in and buy a penny buster. -Well that was roll cut in half with a lump of meat in the middle of it. Penny }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1511169\charrsid11754349 buster}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What would you have in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh bread and jam or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your wife make her own bread or jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 She did - she did several times. Many, many times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about pickles and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh they were cheap enough. Bottle of pickled onions - for tuppence, you know. She used to pickle her own cabbage and her own onions. I used to put the shallots in and then from that she got plenty to pickle you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about wine and beer and medicines - did she make any of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no. Oh - she had a remedy for medicines - yes. I had my own remedy too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about vegetables and fruit - you grew your own shallots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I grew my own - I used to 
- I had allotment you see - paid three shillings a week then for allotment. You could go, Sunday morning you'd go out and she'd say, bring me back some potatoes or cauliflower or whatever you had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you grow all your own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you grow any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. Wouldn't do - you'd have the kids all over the hedge after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you eat any tinned or dried fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Never seen much tinned stuff then. Tin openers were - something out of the fashion then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you keep any hens or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
I had a chicken in the back yard or anything like - you buy it three months 'fore Christmas - don't let it run about, just put it in a wire netting cage and feed it up for fattening for Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That was like your father did before you wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember how many times a week you had meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Four or five times - yes. Liver and bacon once - anything like that. Used to get a lot of ofal in them days -
 you don't get that today. We used to get the chittelings. That was lovely. B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4930161\charrsid11754349 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
t it was taking a lot of washing and cleaning. But - now you don't get the ofal. That's all gone into these - well, in the meat pies too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you get on the side any extra meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh - Highgate you know - not - I used to go over and get a rabbit sometimes in Ken Wood you know. I used to catch 'em with a copper snare - copper wire. See? You could get a rabbit then you could - if you had've sold it you'd only get threepence
 for it. Now you get fifteen bob for one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you or your wife ever go short so your little boy could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, I don't think we - we were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was your little boy allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, he kept silent at meals and - wash his hands 'fore he sat down and - wait for his mother to tell him to start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Could he choose what he ate or did he have to have what was given to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If he his mother asked him what he would like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he have to eat it all up or was he allowed to leave any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh no, he never - force him to eat. That's a very bad thing for a child. Make it - force a child to eat it all up. That's - you don't know how that is - I'm able to explain why he can't eat it in the proper way and 
therefore he might be in pain and that was - no, we never done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was he allowed to ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes. We were always pleased to see that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you teach him to hold his knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. The proper way and how I put it on the plate - when he'd finished. Straight with the fork. Sign that he'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would he bring a book or a toy to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no, no. No. No toys, no books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When did everybody leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Waited - 'til father got up. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have regular places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, kept the same places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What order did your wife serve the food in? Who would she serve first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh the - the little boy first. Then father. And then 
her. She always served herself last. Sometimes I wish she served me last because it was much better - the gravy was thicker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When the little boy was very small before he could fee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4930161\charrsid11754349 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349  himself who fed him - did you or your wife?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh the wife - I never interfered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When your little boy was young did you feel that there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh there's only one way to bring up children, the right way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How would you say that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Make the child obey its parents. And if it obeys its parents it'll obey everything else - in authority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you and your wife share the same ideas about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you talk about ways of bringing up your little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well we used to discuss well what do you think of him today, is he better today and all - all natural family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was there anybody you would talk to if you were particularly worried about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I would go straight to his school mistress. Or the schoolmaster. They were the people that - would know better than anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was your own mother alive when your little boy was small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh she used to come once a week - never missed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ask her advice in bringing him up at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, she left it all to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Do you think you shared the same ideas as your mother about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about your mother-in-law - did you see much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well - you know mother-in-laws, that's a very funny - tric
k - a tricky question you know. I remember - my mother-in-law when her husband died and we buried him, she stood by the grave and the grave diggers lowered him down, she went nearer to look in and nearly fell in but the grave digger put out his hand and h
e says, now one at a time Madam. See, well mothers-in-laws you know they're.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did she have anything to do with the way you brought up your little boy though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, no, we were never - she never interfered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you see very much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 O
h she was me near neighbourhood in fact you see not, we did never quarrelled. But I never had a very wide view on mothers-in-laws - I - I'd rather leave 'em out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children - things li
ke safety, you told me earlier you showed him how to use tools and what they were for, is there anything else you taught him about safety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we didn't have - to bother much about safety on the roads. They were only horses then. In fact some horses w
ould stop rather than go over anybody. There was not much safety to teach about - only - in games and that. Tell 'em not to be too rough and - if they climbing and that - 'cos tree climbing was the - up trees you know, in them days was a proper pastime. S
pecially if there was any apples on the tree.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you teach them that they should eat certain things and not other things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, we left it to the mother to give it - whatever it wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about discipline - you said you think it's most im
portant to bring a child up to respect its parents - what other things about discipline did you teach your boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Be clean - be clean, tidy, tell him not - you know, the most particular thing now, if you go for a job the first thing the person do is to
 look down at your feet - have you ever noticed that? It's from the feet up they take your character. Well I used to and if I saw the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4930161\charrsid11754349  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 man cleaning his boots underneath - I knew he was brought up in the right way. I always now clean my boots - you see. And 
I - I suppose you wouldn't see one in a hundred outside today do that. But that was a part of our discipline.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And you brought your boy up like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you hope that he'd share his worries with you when he got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Never thought about that you know - never thought about him getting old. I never thought I'd get old either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 But when he was a child did you hope that if there was something wrong with him he'd tell you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, I told him always to. I taught him the 
- I taught him the sight of man or the going in the men's toilets and that you know and some men take advantage and I taught him all that. I taught - taught him never to travel in a train if there was only one lady in the carriage. He asked me why when he
 got a bit older. And I told him it was a dangerous thing that the lady would always be believed before the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was there any special way that you hoped he'd behave towards you - how did you want him to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 As his dad - as his fathe
r. And to remember to honour your father and your mother. And he never - that's all - I never rammed things down him, I left it entirely to his teaching and what his mother taught him, but to be tidy, clean and courteous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 When he was little did you and your wife ever manage to leave him so that you could go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would somebody come in to look after him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He'd go into a neighbours house, you see. Tell him to go into Mrs Evans's or somebody's that was - oh, he'd be all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you tell him he should hit back if somebody hit him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes - oh I told him never to let anyone - I said don't you believe that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4930161\charrsid11754349  words of God turning the left }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 cheek - you give it a good blow. Oh yes, oh he wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Were there any children you discouraged him from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Occasionally there were you know. Selfish little - spiteful children you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 If your little boy did something you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That I - well - I - take his pants down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And smack him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 With bare hand. You were - you allowed to do that in them days. And it is good medicine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How often would you think he did something wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh not too often. But if he got that he got good medicine and he'd never d
o it again. They should be doing it today more. Instead of petting them up so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your wife ever smack him as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh - I think so. I never used to speak. She'd give it to him all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Would you say your little boy received the ideas about how to behave mainly from you or from your wife or from both of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
My boy - got it from me. If it - if there'd have been a girl she - she'd have go it from her. But he got it from me. I think you call it the facts of life today. But - the 
facts of life indeed. Amuse me sometimes as I - I was a boy of eighteen 'fore I knew anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 But you think you were mainly the one who gave the ideas to your boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I gave 'em to my boy. Oh I told him - even about medical things. See, th
at - I said you'll be doing what I've done - going and joining the Army and - you'll get - across where there's women and you'll probably - go with 'em and - always if you can wash yourself with your own - urine water. And then you'll never get any troubl
e then. That sort of thing was very prominent in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Can you remember anything you did with your wife and little boy on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we had a great day that day. Christmas tree and - oh yes, we - have a early breakfast and then leave 
it to mother, I'd take him out so mother could get on with the cooking. I'd go down - I'd probably have a turkey given to me you see, knowing so many people in the markets and - I might have one sent as a present. If we didn't we'd wait 'til twelve o'cloc
k Christmas Eve and buy one very cheap - and get one for five bob, seven bob, eight bob, in them days. They had no fridges you see and they used to throw 'em over your head - the one that caught it had to pay for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You played the cornet yourself and the trumpet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I had - I had me own cornet. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you play it very often in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 With the boy I used to teach him, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he play well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. He got to learn it well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did he play any other musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your wife play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, she never bothered much - she had too much work to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you sing together ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh we used to have a song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you have a lot of books or newspapers or magazines in your home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes, I used to have the Boys Own, the Strand. World Wide World.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Was this for your little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh they were all mans too - Wide World was a magazine - Strand was a magazine. We used to get John Bull, Tit Bits, the pink Gazette was the Police Gazette. You got all the police cases in that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 There wasn't many libraries in them days. You never had the free library in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you read aloud to your wife or your little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No. I don't believe in reading aloud. You're under a bit of a - the nut side the when you read aloud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do on Bank Holidays with your little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I would take him out. Take him to the fairground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Up to Hampstead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. Penny on the swings. Penny on the - big wheel - well there wasn't much of a wheel - a penny on the coconut shies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 For how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5207079\charrsid11754349 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
k was the most you could afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you go every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Not every year. You find you couldn't do it every year. You might go for a day in the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Where did you go mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 All along the South Coast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What did you do when you were on holiday with your wife and boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well we'd walk and - I remember one day - going - at East - Whitsun - Whitsun time and that with the Sunday school treat. A}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5207079\charrsid11754349 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
d I'm walking him through a field he hadn't seen much country - more than a bit of round London. And a bird flying over head did something - then it dropped on my hat. I can rem
ember this today. I took it off and I said, look at that Ernie. Isn't that awful? No, dad, he says, you want to thank God cows don't fly. Make a bigger mess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 How did you spend Saturdays in those days when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid815590 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 That's the day - for cleaning. Cleaning the boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You did it - your little boy didn't do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 He did when he got old enough. Clean the knives, clean the doorstep, clean the windowsill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I never did much on a Sunday. The wife would hav
e a cold dinner, you know, bit of lamb or anything. No, we never did much work on - go for a walk over the fields.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you think it wrong to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 No, I never thought that. But it was a - a time when you relaxed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you still go to the Methodist church on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your wife go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 And your little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes. That's why there was no time - cook a dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you still belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Well I got a rather - low voice and I - I give it up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did the church run any temperance club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 
Oh I never believed in that. They run the club but I never joined that. I never believed that - temperance society. I - I believed what God had made he had made 
for man's use and not abuse. So - if he wanted to drink beer or a drink of whisky he could have it if he had it in moderation. I would never join a temperance - I don't believe in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did you belong to any other clubs organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh the Boys Brigade and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 But when you were grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Oh I used to teach 'em then. When I wasn't here - when I was - at London but when I was away soldiering I was - couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 You taught in the Sunday school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 I taught in
 the Brigades. In the drills. Put 'em through drill and that. I taught them - they were the boys the way of life too. You see, in the Bri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5207079\charrsid11754349 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5207079\charrsid11754349 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12870005 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Did your own boy go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15467762 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4472500\charrsid11754349 Yes, yes. He had to bring his little text - he had to bring his little text home every -
